---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About">
  <section class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6 pt-20 pb-24">
    <p class="text-sm font-medium text-neutral-500 uppercase tracking-widest mb-4">About</p>
    <h1 class="text-5xl font-semibold tracking-tight leading-tight">
      We help organizations move from AI curiosity to AI leverage.
    </h1>

    <div class="mt-10 prose prose-lg prose-neutral max-w-none prose-headings:tracking-tight prose-h2:font-semibold prose-h2:text-2xl prose-h2:mt-10">
      <p>
        Datashop is a small consultancy. We work with a small number of teams at a time because transformation isn't a deck — it's a relationship that plays out over months, with the hard conversations included.
      </p>

      <h2>The two shapes of our work</h2>

      <p>
        We've found the engagements we're best at cluster into two shapes. One is <strong>org-wide AI transformation</strong>: working with executive teams to map where AI actually changes the business, what needs to happen across functions, and what operating model survives the change.
      </p>

      <p>
        The other is <strong>MVP to production scale</strong>: picking up an AI system that's working for a few users and building the evaluation, observability, cost, and reliability practices that let it handle real load without cracking. This is the phase most teams are surprised by, and most of what goes wrong happens here.
      </p>

      <h2>How we work</h2>

      <p>
        We parachute in, look at the real problem, and leave you with something durable. That means: a team that understands the system after we've gone, documentation that doesn't lie, and a measurement setup that tells you when things are drifting.
      </p>

      <p>
        We don't take every engagement. If the fit's wrong we'll say so — and refer you to someone better suited.
      </p>

      <h2>Get in touch</h2>
      <p>
        Tell us what you're working on. <a href="/contact">Start a conversation →</a>
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
